Lokoja –   Gov. Yahaya Bello of Kogi. has approved the appointment of Justice Henry Olusuyi as the acting Chief Judge (CJ), of the state. Mr Onogwu Mohammed, Chief Press Secretary to Bello, confirmed the appointment in a statement issued on Friday in Lokoja. Mohammed said Olusuyi would function in that capacity pending the appointment of a substantive CJ. The position became vacant, following the death of Justice Nasir Ajanah on June 29. Similarly, the appointment of Justice Bayo Olowosegun as the acting President of the state’s Customary Court of Appeal by the governor, was also announced in the statement. Olowosegun’s appointment also followed the demise of former occupant of the office, Justice Shaibu Atadoga, who died on June 22. Both appointments are for an initial period of three months, the government disclosed in the statement. (NAN) ABUJA - The National Judicial Council (NJC) on Tuesday directed the most senior judges in the Rivers High Court and Customary Court of Appeal to oversee the assigning cases to judges. This is contained in a statement signed by Mr Soji Oye, Acting Director of Information, NJC’s office, in Abuja.… June 3, 2014 In "News" By Muhammad Nasir Bello   Sokoto -  Gov. Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto state, has approved the appointment of Justice Sa’idu Sifawa as Acting Chief Judge of the state. A statement issued to newsmen on Tuesday, by Tambuwal’s Director General, Media and Public Affairs Malam Abubakar Shekara, said the appointment is… January 1, 2019 In "Politics" …Accuses Edo CJ of attempt to supplant nominees with cronies Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigerian Bar Association, Benin Branch, has appealed to the National Judicial Council (NJC) to resist plots by the Edo State government to influence the appointment of its preferred candidates into the state’s judiciary. In a… May 4, 2020 In "News"